The paper deals with change detection in multi-band images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.MM). The proposed method involves modeling the observed images as spatial and spectral versions of two latent images, which is a common approach in image restoration (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of a block-coordinate descent algorithm, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of sensor dissimilarity, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
